I decided to aggressively contend for the center. I was expecting 6. exd5, Nxd5, 7. Bxd5, Qxd5.

c4 - threatens the knight at d5. My options are: Nb6, Nf4, Nf6. I did not want to return the knight to f6 and allow white to pressure on the queenside. I avoided b6 because I really wanted to attack white's kingside and b6 would put the knight out of position. Therefore I decided on Nf4.

a6 is designed to limit the Knight's mobility. I probably should have moved Bc5
